                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="114273" author="thomasd" created="Tue, 7 Apr 2015 02:29:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We could also add support for ReactiveStreams on top of this, if we would include the adapter from &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/ReactiveX/RxJavaReactiveStreams&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://github.com/ReactiveX/RxJavaReactiveStreams&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="115302" author="thomasd" created="Wed, 6 May 2015 08:08:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We need some further discussions how to proceed with this.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="118797" author="jnarloch" created="Sun, 23 Aug 2015 14:03:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hey, &lt;br/&gt;
I just wanted to say that from user perspective, this looks like a very interesting feature. Being able, for instance to easly compose multiple queries in parallel would be clearly an advantage. At this point I only wonder if some more complex use cases then just returning whole content of the database are going to work? Like for instance pagination - skiping or limiting the number of entries?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I just wondering, since you already have made most of the effort, why you haven&apos;t merge this? &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="128471" author="mp911de" created="Wed, 6 Apr 2016 09:33:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=jnarloch&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;jnarloch&quot;&gt;Jakub Narloch&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;we&apos;re investigating further on a end-to-end solution. Our goal is supporting persistence technologies using a reactive driver with true reactive behavior. Thomas&apos; PR converts an iterable to emit data calling operations in a blocking manner.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="131812" author="mp911de" created="Fri, 2 Sep 2016 07:08:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Closing this ticket because reactive support is continued with &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/browse/DATACMNS-836&quot; title=&quot;Add components to support reactive repositories&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;DATACMNS-836&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;DATACMNS-836&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. We will provide native reactive support using reactive drivers. A conversion of scalar values or futures into reactive wrapper types is not intended.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
